A looming mass below. Eepret peered down into the depths, past the stream of silent fish, past the rising tendrils of branching kelp, into the darkness that was all things.

"It will soon be ready."

His companions followed him downwards as they drifted towards the vast contour. Their passage was indistinguishable from a current. A faint purple glow rose from the structure, dwarfing them into motes of debris.

As they approached, they started to make out the veins and pathways of activity, spreading across the surface in an endless pulsing network of energy.

